  "text": "Novacrystals are an equipment material in Monster Hunter Wilds. You’ll have a chance at collecting them from mining outcrops once you reach High Rank or earn them as rewards for certain High Rank hunts.You’ll need novacrystals to forge weapons like the Final Battleaxes and armor like the Gypceros Coil.Our Monster Hunter Wilds guide will tell you where to find novacrystals and how to collect them.Where to find novacrystals in Monster Hunter WildsImage: Capcom via PolygonNovacrystals come from the mining outcrops that you can find everywhere. You’ll find them in Windward Plains, Scarlet Forest, Oilwell Basin, Iceshard Cliffs, and the Ruins of Wyveria — every region in the game.Mining outcrops appear on your map with a blue icon. Open your map and hit right on the D-pad twice. Scroll down through the filter to look for mining outcrops, use left and right on the D-pad to scroll through the options, and set one as the waypoint for your seikret.Image: Capcom via PolygonYou can collect an item three times from each mining outcrop before it’s exhausted. Mining outcrops refresh every 15 minutes or so. Novacrystals are pretty rare, so you will probably have to check several mining outcrops to find some.Image: Capcom via PolygonYou also have a (small) chance of collecting a novacrystal when you destroy the crest of a Gypceros.Finally, novacrystals are a (possible) reward for come High Rank hunts like:Hunting an HR Rey Dau in “When the Dust Settles …”Hunting an HR Nu Udra in “Sinister Sneer”Hunting an Arkveld in “The Chains of Life”Hunting an HR Ajarakan and a gravios in “Troublemakers”Hunting an HR Xu Uu and Guardian Ebony Odogaron in “The Struggle to Surive”How to collect extra mining outcrop resourcesIn Monster Hunter Wilds armors, talismans, and decorations all give you skills. At level 3, the Geologist skill gets you one extra item from mining outcrops per time you interact with them.Equipment like the Geology Charm talisman, Chainmail armor, and Geology Jewel decorations all give you the Geologist skill. For mining outcrops, you only get a benefit at the third level of the skill, so you’ll need three pieces that give you the skill — like the Chainmail Headgear, Armor, and Gloves.The Geologist skill also doesn’t add to the number of times you can collect something from a mining outcrop — you still only collect three times per visit. It does, however, increase the number of items you pull out with each time you hit Circle/B.To also help you understand Monster Hunter Wilds, we explain how to capture monsters, how to change weapons, provide some Seikret tips, and teach you how layered armor works.",
